article.headline: Will Baker and Jordan Wright combine for 33 points to lead LSU to 75-63 win over North Florida

images.name: Trae Hannibal elevates for the big-time stuff
images.caption: Trae Hannibal elevates for the big-time stuff

article.linkText: Will Baker and Jordan Wright combine for 33 points to lead LSU to 75-63 win over North Florida
article.story: BATON ROUGE, La. -- — Will Baker scored 18 points, Jordan Wright added 15 and LSU beat North Florida 75-63 on Friday night. Baker and Wright were a combined 9-of-22 shooting from the floor. Wright made a pair of 3-pointers and made 5 of 6 from the line. Baker hit 8 of 10 free throws and had eight rebounds. Tyrell Ward added 14 points and Mike Williams III had 11 for LSU (4-2). Jalen Reed grabbed nine rebounds and had five assists. Jaylen Smith scored 13 points and Max Hrdlicka had nine, each with all of his points in the second half, to lead North Florida (4-3). LSU never trailed, led 36-18 at the break and had a 30-point lead with 13:56 remaining. An 11-0 run, capped by consecutives 3s from Hrdlicka, pulled the Ospreys to 68-59 with 3:44 left. Ward answered with a 3-pointer and Williams a jumper to stretch the lead to 14 points with 2:08 to play. LSU will look for its fourth straight win when it travels to Syracuse for a Tuesday matchup. North Florida plays at Iowa on Wednesday. ------ Get poll alerts and updates on AP Top 25 basketball throughout the season.
